If we examine the problems with Canada's socialism it all comes down to provinces wanting more control.  I am a firm beleiver in one strong central government for the people.  However this will only happen if by some fantastically odd twist of fate we get a majority NDP government with a Prime Minister with the balls to start recinding provincial rights and taking over the resources and industry of the richer provinces.<br>
