<br>
The general argument for socialism seems to be the mistaken impression that 'People are equal'.  People are not equal.  All men are, to coin a phrase, NOT created equal.  Certain people have genetic potentials which are different that others.  Some people are born stronger, some faster, some smarter.  Each person has advantages and disadvantages, and it is THEIR job to optimize their skillsets for those advantages.<br>
<br>
I work my ass off to make a very good living at a very young age.  I entered the work force at 16 and have been working full time doing software ever since.  The wonderful government of this fine country/state (/snort) collects close to 40 percent of my paycheck to pay for things I neither want, nor need, for other people.<br>
<br>
Social Security?  It won't be there when I retire.  And I'm already planning for retirement.  I won't need it.  And yet I'm forced to pay for it.  We know it's dying.  All it is is a vestigal system designed to buy pills for people too inept to plan for retirement.<br>
<br>
Welfare?  Even better.  I spend my hard earned money so some prostitute can pop out twelve kids (welfare pays by the kid, dontchaknow) and use the income to pay for drugs.  My hard earned money buys drugs for whores.  Doesn't that make me warm and fuzzy.<br>
<br>
People are not equal.  Go to college, get a damn job and work for your living like everyone else.  There are two basic needs.  Food, shelter (defining clothing as shelter).  There are plenty of homeless shelters (which I support), and anyone can find food.  Hell, churches and charities (which I donate to) hand it out like candy.<br>
<br>
Beyond that?  Toughy lucky. Medicine is expensive, education is a luxury.  Ideally, yes, I'd provide medical care, but PRACTICALLY (something many of you don't seem to be) we can't do it.  There is no system that can be implemented to provide free, good medical care for everyone.<br>
<br>
I like the luxuries in life.  Between my car, EQ accounts, movie tickets, cable plan and cable modem, I probably spend more than enough to support a family or two.  But you know what, and this is the part people aren't going to like?  I'm fine with that.  I work, I buy things I like and enjoy them.  My ability to drive in style, enjoy quality TV and play EQ is, quite frankly, more important to me in the grand scheme of things than some gutter-trash who decides her crack is more important to her than her career.<br>
<br>
I was raised to work.  Taught to learn.  I went to crappy schools, but I didn't learn there.  I learned in books.  Public libraries are free, and from them I derived enough knowledge to make a good life for myself.  There is no reason anyone else in the US can't do the same, except Laziness.  And there is no way you can tell me it's fair to make me pay for other peoples' laziness. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkerplanes>DarkerPlanes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/03 8:50:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   this post is still here?</span><hr size=1> my god, I can't believe this post is still here.... lol<br>
