<br>
Not to sidetrack into an exestentalist and Marxists viewpoints here, but...just throwing out food for thought.<br>
<br>
A.  Assets ARE monitary weath IF they can be tranfered into money.  Hence, sell a home, get a few million dollars (money, itself...just transfered into a different form, still the same on your financial statement in either form..thus STILL overall 'monitary' WEALTH).<br>
<br>
<br>
B.  If someone is well educated and intelligent, they COULD very well be BROKE their whole life...but NEVER poor.  Education is a form of wealth (due to INCREASED quality of life...another FORM of wealth).  Some people use it and some do not. <br>
<br>
Or if you want to talk about economics itself per authoritarian socialism,  as in the U.S.S.R., The Union of Soviet SOCIALIST (NOT communist) Republic.  Karl Marx theorizes on (autoritarian socialisim AS pre-communism tranferance) that in economy, QUANTITY (of goods OR actions) EFFECT quality.  Thus, the more, the RICHER (monitarily OR lifestyle wise).  Or the OVER production...causing lack of demand and low economic states.<br>
<br>
As for DEMOCRATIC Socialism...well, I don't have much to add that has not already been discussed.  Plus I have a patient in 5 minutes, LOL!  <br>
<br>
But I will say this, when I was younger I though it was a GREAT theory.  Now that I have seen it in practice, I think that QUALITY (of life, healthcare, education) go DOWN for eveyone under a democratic socialist system.<br>
<br>
  My husband who is English disagrees.  He like the idea of EVERYONE getting medical care, become better educated when they want/need it (like he had in England).  I think that (in the US at least) we STILL have that.  Medicare pays for people with health problems who can NOT afford.  State University systems give GRANTS (no LOANS) for people to attend collage if they can not afford it, etc.  So I see no NEED to tax us all to over 50% when we already ARE taking care of people that need to be helped.  JMO<br>
<br>
But ya know...a lot DOES come down into what you are born into.  Education (among other things...primarly travel and age) can manipulate it.  Either way though...that's life.  Some people have a CHOICE to create their own paths and some people DO NOT (in places where they are TOLD what to do and ONLY what to do and are not educated enough to know the get the hell outa there and strive for more). <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaSig.gif"><br><br><b><font face="garamond" size=3><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543802">My Magelo Profile</a></center><font size=0 font face=garamond font color=black></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 1/22/03 9:08:04 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caenn>Caenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 9:44:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: idiot socialists</span><hr size=1> Wow!  This is an awesome thread.  Too bad I happened across it so late <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->       .  I'm not going to pick apart every comment in every post.  I'd be here all night.  Just going to add my two cents on a few comments that caught my eye.  I'm sure this will nonetheless turn into a very long post.  Sorry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.g