I'd like to make two points right up front:<br>
     <br>
     1) Others have touched on the point that pure capitalism is not necessarily feasible and must be regulated by some form of socialism.  I most definately agree with this concept, though the degree to which it must be regulated is a matter for debate.  Just know that when I refer to &quot;capitalism&quot;, I am referring to it in this context.<br>
     <br>
     2) While it may be &quot;cliche&quot; and smack of &quot;rhetorical, brainwashed drivel&quot; (as will other parts of this post) and serve as fodder for some of the over-educated pseudo-intelligent types out there, like it or not, a society centered around the free market economy has made the United States of America (arguably) the most powerful nation that has ever existed at any time in history.  And it's happened in a relative flash-in-the-pan of 200 or so years.<br>
    <br>
Well, here we go...<br>
